      • update

        public void update()
        This method is to be invoked when the user data has changed and the appearance/name of the node requires to be updated. This does not update the visual appearance! Therefore, invoke the tree's updateNode() method.

      • setDate

        public void setDate(double date)
        This method works only for performance instructions, i.e. elements in an MPM map. It sets its date to the specified value and triggers the parent map to reorder its list of elements accordingly. This does not update the visual appearance! Therefore, invoke the tree's updateNode() method with the parent tree node.
        Parameters:
        date -
